<h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-2 leading-tight">Words Only in TWL</h1>
<p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8 not-prose">Dictionary · Anagram</p>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-15">June 15, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-300 dark:bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>5 min read</span>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">While SOWPODS is the larger dictionary, TWL does contain a small number of words that aren't accepted in international play. Understanding these TWL-exclusive entries matters if you switch between tournament contexts or play on platforms that use different word lists.</p>

      <!-- Stat strip -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">~187,000</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Total TWL words</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">~300</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TWL-only words</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">NASPA</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Governing body</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">What Is the Tournament Word List?</h2>
      <p>TWL — sometimes called TWL06, OWL, or simply "the tournament list" — is maintained by NASPA (North American Scrabble Players Association). It's the only dictionary permitted in sanctioned tournaments across the United States and Canada. The current edition (TWL06) draws from Merriam-Webster's Official Scrabble Players Dictionary and undergoes periodic updates.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Fact</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">TWL is <span class="text-white font-medium">curated for North American tournament play</span>. Words must appear in approved Merriam-Webster sources, and the list excludes terms considered offensive — a policy SOWPODS does not apply.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">How TWL Differs from SOWPODS</h2>
      <p>The most common misconception is that SOWPODS simply contains everything in TWL plus extras. In reality, a small set of words exists only in TWL — words that NASPA accepted but Collins lexicographers excluded from their international list.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">📖 TWL Characteristics</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">~187,000 words. North American sources. Offensive words removed. Updated by NASPA committee. Required for US/Canadian tournaments.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🌍 SOWPODS Characteristics</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">~276,000 words. Global English sources. All words retained regardless of offence. Updated by Collins. Used everywhere else worldwide.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>These TWL-only words typically fall into categories: recent American slang adopted by Merriam-Webster but not yet by Collins, proper nouns that TWL reclassified as common words, and technical terms from American industry or culture.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Examples of TWL-Only Words</h2>
      <p>The number of TWL-exclusive words is far smaller than SOWPODS exclusives, but they do exist. Here are notable examples:</p>

